      <processinfo id="aspace_f51664d5c0b836f3eb5a7805c2e2d0d2">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_ac68a0073a55e50e4ec038028a2aeb94">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The collection contains photographs, slides, and pictures of Davenport College and Pierson College at Yale. Included are interior and exterior views, views of the masters' houses, dining halls, and courtyards, as well as photographs documenting construction.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_a826c90f670a3f532153ee7691390212">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The materials are arranged in two series: I. Construction Progress Photographs, 1930-1932. II. General Views, circa 1930-1969.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_69c9fc95b938faf2e858952c46ba9401">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
